{
  "texts": [
    "An alternative to the computationally intensive generation process is causal matching, where the example is paired with a similar control example that has a different concept value (Roberts et al., 2020; Zhang et al., 2023; Gat et al., 2023).",
    "In contrast, model-specific methods typically intervene on the latent space of the explained model (Ravfogel et al., 2020; Feder et al., 2021; Elazar et al., 2021; Haghighatkhah et al., 2022; Kumar et al., 2022; Wu et al., 2023a; Zhao et al., 2023a), or train a proxy model that mimics the CF behavior of the explained model (Wu et al., 2023a).",
    "What: input-output, local How: intrinsic, specific, text",
    "We define Natural Language Explanations (NLE) as any textual explanation extracted or generated by an NLP system that is used for justifying its own prediction.",
    "We do not consider generative models used to explain other model predictions as an NLE method."
  ]
}